cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "VerdictAI: An AI Legal Reasoning Platform for Nepali Law"
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Pradhan"
    given-names: "Manseez B."
  - family-names: "Basukala"
    given-names: "Pranaya"
  - family-names: "Phaiju"
    given-names: "Riju"
  - family-names: "Raut"
    given-names: "Salon"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Manseez31/VerdictAI"
abstract: >-
  VerdictAI is a retrieval-augmented legal reasoning platform for Nepali law.
  It combines hybrid retrieval (dense embeddings + BM25 fused with Reciprocal
  Rank Fusion) over official Nepali Acts with citation-grounded answer
  generation, an independent LLM judge for faithfulness scoring, bilingual
  (Nepali/English) output, and a multi-agent Legal Case Intelligence Suite that
  produces educational case analyses.
keywords:
  - legal-tech
  - retrieval-augmented-generation
  - nepali-law
  - multi-agent-systems
  - large-language-models
